text.section:
A licensed veterinarian who vaccinates a dog, cat, or ferret against rabies:
May select the vaccine to be used;
Shall administer the vaccine in a manner that is consistent with the recommendations of the National Association of State Public Health Veterinarians;
Shall issue to the owner of the dog, cat, or ferret a vaccination certificate, on the form that the Department approves; and
Shall keep a record of the vaccination for a period of 5 years.
